cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.PF, cs.NI, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper is primarily focused on scheduling parallel tasks on a cluster platform, which falls under the scope of distributed and parallel computing. 
2. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the optimization of two criteria, makespan and weighted minimal average completion time, which are related to system performance and control. 
3. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper proposes an algorithm for scheduling jobs on a cluster platform with the aim of improving performance. 
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - Although not the main focus, the paper may involve some aspects of networking and internet architecture in the context of cluster computing. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a new algorithm for scheduling jobs on a cluster platform, which falls under the scope of data structures and algorithms.
